SIMPLE: photogenic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Photogenic
<hw>Pho`to*gen"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of
or pertaining to photogeny; producing or generating light.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Appearing attractive in a photograph; having
features that appear attractive in a photograph.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Caused by light, as for example a
skin abnormality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Photogeny</ent>⟦br⟧
